<br>
They wouldn't have to be anything epic, just quests that would take you a lot of places that you wouldn't normally go to.  So it wouldn't be:<br>
<br>
Get X item that drops off a random mob in Velks.  Thats someplace you'd already be and it really wouldn't be a &quot;quest&quot; if you were just there grinding and looted it.<br>
<br>
Maybe have them sneak into permafrost or mistmoore instead, or one of the many other under utilized (and usually really cool) midlevel zones and get something.  <br>
<br>
You should have to go to places that are far apart (half of the fun is getting there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) and when you complete the quest it isn't an uber item or weapon or armor or anything.  Just a cool novelty item.<br>
<br>
Like a ring that can cast minor illusion or goggles that can cast bind sight.   Just cool, kind of fun stuff like that.<br>
<br>
The main thing is though, these are quests that you can do alone if you're higher level to get away from the grinding and raiding.  You can go off, spend a couple days working on it yourself and actually get something done <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> on your own</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
And if you're mid level and want to do them, nothing is stopping you, you're just going to need a little help.<br>
<br>
--<br>
<br>
I guess a good comparison would be the difference between doing the burning rapier quest at level 30 and at level 50.  That kind of thing. <p><b><a href=mailto:Glip@thesafehouse.org><font size="5">Glip the Gnome</font></a></b><br>
